01/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- As scheduled, the EU took over NATO's peacekeeping mission in Macedonia on Monday (31 March).
The event was marked by an official ceremony in Skopje attended by EU security chief Javier Solana, NATO Secretary General George Robertson and Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou.
While in Skopje, Solana met with Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski and Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 01/04/03;
AP, AFP, MIA, A1 TV - 31/03/03)
